deck: Forged by Nissa from the four most powerful swords to destroy Sela's fairy tale book.
description:
In an attempt to protect the Earth from travelling Highborns, the Council of the Five Realms decided to destroy the remaining portals between the five realms (Earth, Neverland, Wonderland, Oz and Myst). Sela's fairy tale book was one of those portals. It fell upon Nissa to create a weapon powerful enough to destroy the book. Seeing as no single sword could do the deed, she used her powers to combine four of the most powerful swords (Excalibur, Kusanagi, Mistilteinn and Chrysaor) into one. This one she called Lysraseri, 'The Light's Rage'.

Each of the gems respresents one of the original swords and the power it brings.

  • The green gem is for the Kusanagi and heals its wielder.
  • The blue gem is for Mistilteinn and makes the sword appear whenever it is needed.
  • The gold gem is for Chrysaor and his the ability to purify.
  • The red gem is for Excalibur and taps into the inextinguishable flames.
name: Lysraseri

deck: Deathstroke is often seen donning a mask or helmet, the most recognizable piece to his costume.
description:
Arrow

Deathstroke's Mask is seen multiple times in island flashbacks, and Deathstroke wears a new version of the mask when he returns to Starling City. The original island mask is made out of a cloth material, while the new mask is more metallic.

Also, when Slade recruits an army in season 2 he gives his soldiers masks, very similar to his own.

Batman: Arkham Origins

Slade bears a blue and orange mask in the video game Batman: Arkham Origins. This mask appears to have a latex coating on the outside, and is made of some type of metal or other hard material.

Injustice: Gods Among Us

A different version of the mask also appears in the video game "Injustice: Gods Among Us". This mask features a red robotic eye, not unlike the New 52 version of Slade.

Mortal Kombat vs. DC Universe

Slade wears a slightly different version of the mask in another video game, "Mortal Kombat vs. DC Universe".

New 52

Deathstroke wears a blue and orange mask with a robotic red eye in the New 52. The mask can also flip up, revealing Slade's face.

deck: Nozarashi is the zanpakutō of Kenpachi Zaraki, Captain of the 13 Court Guard's 11th Division in the Soul Society.
description:
The Nozarashi (野晒, Nozarashi) is a zanpakutō from the manga series BLEACH that was created by Tite Kubo. The series first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shonen Jump in August 2001. Nozarashi first appeared in BLEACH Volume 8, CH. 65 "Collisions".

The zanpakutō (斬魄刀, zanpakutō) is the primary weapon of all Soul Reapers. While normal Soul Reapers are given a base asauchi (浅打ち, asauchi) to impart their soul onto. Although, Kenpachi stole his zanpakutō from a member of the 13 Court Guard that he killed.

The name translates as "Weather Beaten".

Weapon Evolution

All zanpakutō have three separate forms, but the final two can only be obtained through strict training. Not every Soul Reaper is capable of activating the final two forms.

Sealed Form

A sealed for is the first stage of all zanpakutō. This is based from the original asauchi a Soul Reaper is given in the academy. It will often change as the Soul Reaper imparts their soul and power into it. Kenpachi was first found as a young boy with the sword that he had stolen off a Soul Reaper he had killed.

For much of the series, Kenpachi was willfully ignorant to even attempting to evolve the abilities of his zanpakutō and depended on his very own brute strength.

Shikai Form

Shikai (始解, shikai) is the first of the seals on a zanpakutō. Activating this power is gained by learning the name of the sword. This is done through extensive training. Upon speaking the name of the zanpakutō, it will take on a new form with unique abilities.

Kenpachi eventually learned the name of his zanpakutō through his training with Captain Unohana and struck her down.

It first appeared in BLEACH Vol. ?? Ch. 577 "BLADE".
name: Nozarashi

description:
Several hundred magical items crafted by the Xialoin Dragons to combat evil, most of the Wu were crafted by Grandmaster Dashi to combat the Heylin witch Wuya.

List of Shen Gon Wu

  • Ants in the Pants - Releases a swarm of ants that specifically target an opponents pants.
  • Black Beetle - Becomes a fire proof suit of armor.
  • Cannon Blaster - Turns the user into a firable cannonball.
  • Cat's Eye Draco - An elemental Shen Gon Wu that increases the potency of Fire based moves, weapons, and Shen Gon Wu.
  • Changing Chopsticks - Allows the user to shrink to the size of a grain of rice.
  • Crest of the Condor - An elemental Shen Gon Wu that increases the potency of Wind based moves, weapons, and Shen Gon Wu.
  • Crouching Cougar - One of the many transportation Shen Gon Wu, The Crouching Cougar is a jungle transport.
  • Crystal Glasses - Gives the user the ability to see into the future.
  • Denshi Bunny - Gives the user to ability to turn into living electricity.
  • Eagle Scope - Gives the user the ability to focus on certain information in the Fountain of Hui.
  • Emperor Scorpion - Gives the user the abiltiy to control other Shen Gon Wu.
  • Eye of Dashi - Gives the user the ability to shoot lightning.
  • Falcon's Eye - Gives the user the ability to see through walls.
  • Fancy Feet - Fancy Feet are sandals that give the user super speed.
  • Fist of Tebigong - A gauntlet with a clenched fist that gives the user a super strength punch.
  • Fountain of Hui - The fountain contains literally all the information on any subject. Without the compliment Shen Gon Wu the Eagle Scope, the fountain will give random information.
  • Gills of Hamachi - Gives the user the ability to breathe underwater.
  • Glove of Jisaku - Allows the user to use the glove like a powerful magnet.
  • Golden Finger - Allows the user to freeze targets in place for a short period of time.
  • Golden Tiger Claws - The Golden Tiger Claws allow the user to teleport themselves to anywhere in the world by slashing open a portal. This portal can go to anywhere on Earth and even to the center of the Earth.
  • Heart of Jong - The heart can bring inanimate objects to life. It also serves as the basis for the demon Mala Mala Jong.
  • Helmet of Jong - Allows the user to see behind them.
  • Hodoku Mouse - Allows the user to fix any mistake.
  • Jetbootsu - Allows the user to defy gravity.
  • Ju-Ju Flytrap - Allows the user to attack targets with a swarm of flies.
  • Kaijin Charm - An elemental Shen Gon Wu that increases the potency of Water based moves, weapons, and Shen Gon Wu.
  • Kuzusu Atom - This Wu can destroy any object down to the molecular level. This includes other Shen Gon Wu.
  • Lasso Boa Boa - A constricting lasso in the shape of a boa constrictor.
  • Longhorn Taurus - An elemental Shen Gon Wu that increases the potency of Earth based moves, weapons, and Shen Gon Wu.
  • Longi Kite - Allows the user to fly via the dragon wings on the kite.
  • Lotus Twister - Allows the user to stretch their limbs like rubber.
  • Lunar Locket - The Lunar Locket can be used to control the phases of the moon.
  • Manchurian Musca - Allows the user to become a fly.
  • Mantis Flip Coin - Allows the user to jump and flip through their air with the grace of a mantis. This was the first Shen Gon Wu to activate.
  • Mikado Arm - Gives the user super strength by increasing the muscle mass of their arms.
  • Mind Reader Conch - Allows the user to read the minds of others.
  • Moby Morpher - Allows the user to shape shift into almost anything. This Wu is described as one of the most powerful.
  • Monarch Wings - The companion Wu to the mosaic scales.
  • Monkey Staff - Allows the user to have the grace and agility of a monkey and even gains a prehensile tail. This is Jack Spicer's most used Shen Gon Wu.
  • Monsoon Sandals - This Wu stretches the users legs so they can take a kilometer in one step.
  • Moonstone Locust - Allows the user to shoot an army of stone locusts to destroy plant-life.
  • Mosaic Scale - This Wu serves as a prison for the demonic earwig named Sabbini.
  • Orb of Tornami - The orb holds back a mighty flood that can be controlled. Someone with water based chi can cause the orb to shoot ice.
  • Reversing Mirror - Allows the uder to reverse the effects of any Shen Gon Wu. Example the Serpents tail can turn ghost solid, the changing chopsticks make people into giants, and the Two Ton Tunic would float.
  • Ring of the Nine Dragons - Allows the user to split himself into at most nine duplicates of them-self. The downside of the Wu is that it splits everything equally like intelligence, potential, ability, and so forth.
  • Rio Reverso - Allows the user the ability to turn a substance or object into a previous form. Example a football will become a pig and oil will become a dinosaur.
  • Ruby of Ramses - Grants the user the power of telekinesis.
  • Sands of Time - Allows the user to travel through time.
  • Sapphire Dragon - The literal last resort Wu. The sapphire dragon is a sentient Wu that will actively hunt targets and turn them into sapphire statues which it can then control like a zombie army. It must be encased in soot to keep it from activating as it could dominate the world.
  • Serpent's Tail - Grants the user the power of phasing through walls.
  • Shadow Slicer - Allows the user to manipulate their own shadow.
  • Shadow of Fear - Allows the user to see and bring to life a targets worst fear.
  • Shard of Lightning - The user is allowed to travel at super speed for the duration of a flash of lighting.
  • Shen-Ga-Roo - One of the many transportation Wu, this one models a kangaroo with the users riding inside the pouch.
  • Shroud of Shadows - A blanket that can turn the user invisible.
  • Silk Spitter - Allows the user to shoot spider like webbing to either entangle a target, or web swing.
  • Silver Manta Ray - One of the transportation Shen Gon Wu, The Silver Manta Ray can fly and swim underwater. It is often used when Dojo is unavailable.
  • Sphere of Yun - The user can trap an enemy inside an impervious force field which transfers the powers and possessions to the one who holds the Wu.
  • Star Hanabi - The user can shoot and control fire to an extent.
  • Sun Chi Lantern - The user can combine his chi with the chi of anyone illuminated by the light. This allowed Omi to use the signature powers of the other xiaolin warriors.
  • Sweet Baby Among Us - A Wu often used as a last resot, the baby grows to giant size and has super strength as well as the ability to fire entangling diapers at enemies. The shaolin warriors use the Wu as a training exercise.
  • Sword of the Storms - A blade that can cause tornadoes and powerful gusts of wind.
  • Tangle Web Comb - The user can shoot masses of hair that can entangle a target. This Wu needs to be used with absolute focus otherwise it will turn on the user.
  • Third-Arm Sash - The sash acts as a third arm that the user can control. The sash can extend to a certain amount.
  • Thorn of Thunderbolt - The user can shoot rings of electricity.
  • Tongue of Saiping - Allows the user to talk to and control animals.
  • Tunnel Armadillo - One of the transportation Shen Gon Wu that allows the user to travel underground.
  • Two-Ton Tunic - Once activated the tunic becomes an impenetrable suit of armor that weighs approximately 2 tons.
  • Wings of Tinabi - The user grips the handle and the wings propel the user into the air leaving a rainbow trail behind them.
  • Woozy Shooter - The user can fire a gas that confuses the target making them "woozy".
  • Wushan Geyser - The user can selectively erase memories from targets within a short distance.
  • Wushu Helmet - The user can deflect projectiles with this helmet.
  • Yang Yo-Yo - The yo-yo allows the user to travel to a negative world called the Ying-Yang World. If this Wu is not used with the Ying Yo-Yo the user will leave their good side in the Ying-Yang world.
  • Ying Yo-Yo - The yo-yo allows the user to travel to a negative world called the Ying-Yang World. If this Wu is not used with the Yang Yo-Yo the user will leave their good side in the Ying-Yang world.
  • Zing Zom-Bone - This Shen Gon Wu can turn anyone into a mindless zombie servant to the one who holds the shen gon wu.
name: Shen Gon Wu

deck: A book based off of the information created by Cain that mastered the method of killing Through Self Supremacy. It took centuries to be refined into what it is now and made famous by the character Luther Strode.
description:
Conception and History

Sometime during several millennium BC, Cain killed his younger brother (Abel) and discovered the mastery of the flesh through murder. His new-found knowledge from the event changed him drastically, and Cain began to see the world in a whole new light/way. As new perceptions were opened for Cain and he embarked on a new path of enlightenment in life........he began documenting (simply at first, such as pictures and diagrams on parchment for example) what was to become known as "the method" which continued for apparent centuries.

Cain discovered an underlying and universal truth to life: we are all meat for the slaughter and that was basic human nature. Understanding of the human body (and anatomy), understanding of the way of life (human behavioral patterns and psyche), and ultimately understanding of how to end an individual's life any way possible (physically and as violently as possible), was eventually archived by Cain himself and passed down to others (through teachings) who would become his followers.

Those who could understand and duplicate parts of his teachings through learning and practice......became talented in the art. As such The Hercules Method was born, handed down from practitioner to practitioner over countless centuries back as far as the Roman Imperium to 12th century England with it finally making it to the turn of the modern era.

Details

  • "the method" (which is short for 'The Hercules Method' ) was distributed ( in booklet form) by an individual named "the Librarian" apparently for decades. It is speculated on how. Presumably as a 'mail order' type of item.
  • The individual named Luther Strode was the first person in decades to understand/use "the method" to success out of thousands, and possibly hundred of thousands,

deck: A sonic knife to pierce the symbiotes and kill the hosts.
description:
History

Separation Anxiety

When Eddie Brock was later separated from the Venom symbiote by the government, Scream and the other Five Symbiotes broke him out of prison and kidnapped him in a last ditch effort to communicate with their alien "others." Unfortunately Eddie refused to aid them, due to Carnage's example that his "children" became psychopathic killers. After Agony was mysteriously killed, supposedly by Brock, Phage went on a rampage to avenge her by killing Brock. Phage wound up dying however under similarly mysterious circumstances because of a sonic knife that could cut through symbiotes. As it turned out, Scream's host, Donna, had snapped from a possible case of schizophrenia and her symbiote's influence, now believing that the symbiotes and any who host them were evil. She tried misleading the other symbiotes into thinking Eddie Brock was picking them off, but she eventually lost her patience and went on to kill the rest of the symbiote hosts. Scream was about to kill Brock, until the Venom symbiote arrived for its host and merged with Brock again. Together as Venom, they defeated Scream who later wound up being apprehended by federal agents.

deck: When Jason is resurrected and becomes the Red Hood, he uses a dagger that becomes quite specific to him.
description:
Description

The blade is curved in a unique waved shape and resembles a kris or a keris dagger. There are many legends or beliefs surrounding the Kris/Keris blade, and one of those includes the idea that "the blade gives complete invulnerability to its owner."

History

In Red Hood: Lost Days, this dagger is given to Jason as a gift by Talia al Ghul. She tells him it is a replica of one her father used to carry. We also learn in Under the Hood that the blade is extremely sharp.

The dagger Jason carries is both iconic and symbolic of a weapon that was not likely to be found on the streets of Gotham City by many. It also further ties him to the al Ghul family.

deck: The ship that carried baby Lor-Zod to Earth.
description:
Overview

While imprisoned inside the Phantom Zone, the Kryptonian known as General Zod and his mate, Ursa, gave birth to a child named Lor-Zod. While living inside of a transported Kryptonian prison cell known as Fort Rozz, Zod manipulated Phantom Zone technology and created a small space-worthy vessel that could maintain a substantial form and leave the Phantom Zone. As his son was the only Phantom Zoner capable of maintaining a physical form, Zod sent the rocket ship out of the Phantom Zone carrying their young son. The rocket entered Earth's atmosphere and would have crash-landed in the heart of downtown Metropolis, but for the timely arrival of Superman.
name: Lor-Zod Spaceship
